What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Insulin Glargine Market?

Market Analysis and Size

Insulin glargine is long-acting basal insulin given to diabetes patients daily to control blood sugar levels. It consists of microcrystals that slowly release insulin and provide a long duration of action. It is a man-made insulin that is normally produced by the body and helps in the case of diabetes to remove sugar from the blood. It is also used to reduce the sugar-producing ability of the liver.

Data Bridge Market Research analyzes that the global insulin glargine market, which was USD 6,153.50 million in 2022, would rocket up to USD 6,257.70 million by 2030, and is expected to undergo a CAGR of 6.7% during the forecast period of 2023 to 2030. “Single Dose Vial” dominates the type segment of the market owing to the rise in the incidence of diabetes among the population.

